        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:36PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking several thunderstorms
developing from near Philipsburg east to around Harrison with a
stronger cell located near Whitehall. These storms were moving
northeast at 35 mph and will impact much of Jefferson county and
adjacent areas with occasional lightning, brief heavy rainfall and
gusty winds with storms potentially reaching the Helena valley and
Macdonald Pass by around 700 PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, Townsend, Boulder, East Helena, Three Forks, Whitehall,
Montana City, Basin, Toston, Harrison, Rimini, Alhambra, Spring
Meadow Lake State Park, Corbin, Austin, Missouri Headwaters State
Park, Cardwell, Winston, Radersburg, and Silos.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
